is the portal, theoretical restrictions from perturbativity, vacuum\nstability, and unitarity requirements turn out to be important instead and\nexclude much of the region below 100 GeV. For larger DM masses, the THDM II+D\nhas plentiful parameter space that corresponds to interaction cross-sections\nunder the neutrino-background floor and therefore is likely to be beyond the\nreach of future direct searches without directional sensitivity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 12 Sep 2016 19:45:49 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 19 Dec 2016 09:16:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-12-20"}
